This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper describes the use of state-of-the-art models and new data filtering methods to improve translation quality. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is specifically dedicated to NLP research. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data filtering and weighting methods, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
